title: Football: Brick Memorial's Chris Hayes earns Game Ball of Week 5
text:
MORE BRICK Brick Memorialâ€™s 2015 football season opened on the lowest of notes.
After traveling down the road to meet Brick Township in Week 1, the Mustangs departed from Keller Memorial Field with a 36-6 loss and some soul-searching to do.
However, since the season opener, the Mustangs have competed at the level that local football pundits anticipated they would, earning a 52-20 victory over touted Toms River North in Week 2 and downing Lacey and Toms River East in their next two tilts by a combined score of 94-6.
Brick Memorial moved to 4-1 on the year in Week 5 with a hard-fought victory over nonconference foe Old Bridge in a game the Mustangs trailed by three at half
